				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://discuss.userland.com/msgReader$16558&quot;&gt;You can help XML-DEV&lt;/a&gt; get back in the groove, and perhaps learn about current-best-practice in mail servers." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://cryptome.org/mi5-verio.htm&quot;&gt;Cryptome&lt;/a&gt; &quot;learned last evening that Exodus Communications, a major US service provider, ordered last Sunday the removal of a Web site, www.mathaba.net.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://joel.editthispage.com/stories/storyReader$77&quot;&gt;Joel Spolsky&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Good UI designers use consistency intelligently, and, though it may not show off their creativity as well, in the long run it makes users happier.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://discuss.userland.com/flameResistancePolicy&quot;&gt;I finally figured out&lt;/a&gt; how to stop flame-fests once and for all." type="outline"/>
