				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://discuss.userland.com/msgReader$16328&quot;&gt;Jacob Levy&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;There are many more sellers than buyers.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Jacob points to the Smart Money &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.smartmoney.com/marketmap/&quot;&gt;MoneyMap&lt;/a&gt; Java app. Fantastic. I had never seen this before. " type="outline"/>
				<outline text="David Adams &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.xmlrpc.com/discuss/msgReader$795&quot;&gt;posted&lt;/a&gt; an RFC for the xml-rpc interface for his web app spell-checker." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://andrea.editthispage.com/usa/map&quot;&gt;Andrea posted&lt;/a&gt; a map of their vacation route. &quot;The map was composed from 16 smaller maps provided by Expedia using Adobe Photoshop 4.0.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="J William Gurley: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.news.com/Perspectives/Column/0,176,419,00.html?st.ne.per.gif.a&quot;&gt;Can Napster be stopped? No!&lt;/a&gt;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="A brief history of the PC business. Distribution was everything. Retailers everywhere. BusinessLand. Shakeout. What was left standing? Softsel, Micro-D and Ingram. Then Egghead and Dell. Retailers morphed into VARs. Distribution was squeezed to nothing. &lt;i&gt;How will Internet e-commerce &lt;a href=&quot;http://news.cnet.com/news/0-1007-200-1709877.html?tag=st.ne.1002.thed.1007-200-1709877&quot;&gt;shape&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msnbc.com/news/395910.asp?0m=B13Q&quot;&gt;shake&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/i&gt;" type="outline"/>
				</outline>
