				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://weblogs.userland.com/manilaNewbies/discuss/msgReader$2842&quot;&gt;Chris Cothrum groks&lt;/a&gt; the philosophy of Manila." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://dailynews.yahoo.com/h/p/nm/20000416/ts/mdf68374.html&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://static.userland.com/misc/snImages/washingtonPolice.gif&quot; height=&quot;85&quot; width=&quot;46&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; hspace=&quot;8&quot; align=&quot;right&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://dailynews.yahoo.com/h/nm/20000416/ts/imf_leadall_13.html&quot;&gt;Reuters&lt;/a&gt;:  &quot;Police in full riot gear used batons and pepper spray on Sunday in several violent clashes with protesters who were trying to stop meetings of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inessential.com/sheila/2000/04/16&quot;&gt;Sheila&lt;/a&gt; has &quot;dome chunks.&quot; They could come in handy the next time the WTO meets in Seattle." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Wired: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wired.com/news/politics/0,1283,35620,00.html&quot;&gt;Crypto-Convict Won't Recant&lt;/a&gt;. &quot;I once believed it's too bad that there are a lot of people who work for government who are hard-working and honest people who will get hit (by Assassination Politics) and it's a shame,&quot; he says. &quot;Well, I don't believe that any more. They are all either crooks or they tolerate crooks or they are aware of crooks among their numbers.&quot; " type="outline"/>
				<outline text="What is &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.langreiter.com/vanilla/INSTALL&quot;&gt;Vanilla&lt;/a&gt;? &quot;Now we all know that the Web is all about porn^H^H^H^H links.&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://monkeyfist.com/profile/bios.shtml&quot;&gt;MonkeyFist&lt;/a&gt; has a special &lt;a href=&quot;http://a16.monkeyfist.com/&quot;&gt;site&lt;/a&gt; covering today's protests in Washington." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I finally went to see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/chronicle/reviews/movies/AMERICANBEAUTY.DTL&amp;type=printable&quot;&gt;American Beauty&lt;/a&gt; yesterday, what a great movie. Life is more complex than it seems, and then simpler once you get through the complexity." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="On Brdbrain, &lt;a href=&quot;http://brdbrain.editthispage.com/discuss/msgReader$500&quot;&gt;I said&lt;/a&gt;: \&quot;We're in a fast-moving business, right on the precipice of success. We depend on connectivity. Yes, you can expect a cry of pain when the problem isn't being dealt with in a professional manner. Did I say things I regret? Yes I did. But in the bigger picture, we contracted with Conxion for connectivity, and they failed, and they never apologized or issued a credit.\&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I hate (but love) movies with people hanging from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apple.com/trailers/paramount/mission_impossible_2/teaser_lo.html&quot;&gt;precipices&lt;/a&gt;." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Jason Levine's &lt;a href=&quot;http://q.queso.com/deepLeapPlugIn&quot;&gt;DeepLeap Plug-In&lt;/a&gt; for Manila." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Tim O'Reilly: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/a/network/2000/04/13/CFPkeynote.html&quot;&gt;Open source&lt;/a&gt; blah blah blah." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Has &lt;a href=&quot;http://psychcentral.com/bio.htm&quot;&gt;Dr John Grohol&lt;/a&gt; found his &lt;a href=&quot;http://winerlog.editthispage.com/discuss/msgReader$22&quot;&gt;niche&lt;/a&gt;? Kind of embarassing to see a doctor behave this way. Oh well. My own opinion is that sarcasm is better left to &lt;a href=&quot;http://winerlog.editthispage.com/discuss/msgReader$14&quot;&gt;professionals&lt;/a&gt;. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://qube.weblogs.com/&quot;&gt;Qube Quorner&lt;/a&gt; is the first statically-rendered Manila site hosted by UserLand." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://andrea.editthispage.com/usa/sep16&quot;&gt;Andrea&lt;/a&gt; takes us to Capitol Reef National Park in Utah." type="outline"/>
				<outline text="BTW, we've been working on a design for a new Doc Searls weblog. Talking with Doc on the phone yesterday, I said I believe that a picture of Doc must be frontmost on the site. That's the first thing I want to know when I get to a new weblog. Who is the editor? Doc asked me where is my picture? Oy. So there it is, up-top, where it belongs. Click on it to get to my personal page, which I will update more often. " type="outline"/>
				<outline text="An oldie but goodie &lt;a href=&quot;http://surveys.userland.com/surveys/run/dave@userland.com/coffeeSpittingSurvey&quot;&gt;survey&lt;/a&gt; from April 1. Six people said they were Jason Levine! Someone's lying. People never lie on surveys! &lt;i&gt;Do they?&lt;/i&gt;" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="How could someone the same age as someone else conclude the other person is &quot;wise beyond his years&quot;? How could you know?" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="What a &lt;a href=&quot;http://priceclevenger.editthispage.com/&quot;&gt;gorgeous site&lt;/a&gt;." type="outline"/>
